</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="50">3. Carry out additional settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The ShopBuilder also serves to carry out all settings available in the Ceres configuration. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Settings</strong>.<br>
→ The menu <strong>Plugin configuration</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-ceres#20">Setting up Ceres</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Selecting a plugin set in the ShopBuilder</div>
You can select a plugin set from the drop-down list. The page preview displays the settings carried out for the plugin set (e.g. which item is visible).
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="60">4. Creating a page in the ShopBuilder</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The overview of the ShopBuilder offers the possibility of creating and naming new pages for the homepage.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a page:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Create new page</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>Add page</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Page name</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The newly created page is displayed in the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_editing_a_page_in_the_shopbuilder">4.1. Editing a page in the ShopBuilder</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Currently, the overview only enables to edit the name of a page. However, further settings will be available soon.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing the name of a page:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the mouse cursor over the page you want to edit.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Options</strong> button.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Edit</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>Edit</strong> to edit the name of the page.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter any desired name for the page.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_deleting_a_page_in_the_shopbuilder">4.2. Deleting a page in the ShopBuilder</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Pages created in the ShopBuilder can also be removed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a page:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the mouse cursor over the element you want to delete.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Options</strong> button.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Delete</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong> to delete the page.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>Delete</strong> to delete a page.<br>
→ The page is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_deleting_links_of_shopbuilder_pages_to_the_homepage">4.3. Deleting links of ShopBuilder pages to the homepage</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Every page that is created in the ShopBuilder is automatically linked to the homepage. However, the link can be deleted.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a link:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the mouse cursor over the page whose link to the homepage you want to delete.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Options</strong> button.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Deactivate</strong>.<br>
→ The link to the homepage is deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_recreating_links_of_shopbuilder_pages_to_the_homepage">4.4. Recreating links of ShopBuilder pages to the homepage.</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A deleted link of a ShopBuilder page to the homepage can be recreated.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a link:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the mouse cursor over the page that you want to link to the homepage.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Options</strong> button.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Activate</strong>.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the page that you want to link to the homepage.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Deactivate</strong>.<br>
→ The selected page is linked to the homepage.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The blue marking indicates that a link exists.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_duplicating_content">4.5. Duplicating content</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the overview of the ShopBuilder you can duplicate content.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Duplicating content:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The overview of the ShopBuilder opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the mouse cursor over the page whose content you want to duplicate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Options</strong> button.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Duplicate content</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Duplicate content</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-duplicate-content">Table 4</a>.</p>
</li>
