<h2 id="100">15. Scripts in the text widget</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to use JavaScript scripts in the online store, you can implement <strong>&lt;script2&gt;</strong> tags in the text widget of the ShopBuilder. This tag functions like a common &lt;script&gt; tag. ¤For the documentation of the framework used for the ShopBuilder, see <a href="https://github.com/taoeffect/vue-script2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlightjs highlight"><code class="language-plenty hljs" data-lang="plenty">&lt;script2 src="https://momentjs.com/downloads/moment.js"&gt;&lt;/script2&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Explanation</strong>: Here a &lt;script2&gt; tag is used only with the src attribute to load an external script.</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlightjs highlight"><code class="language-plenty hljs" data-lang="plenty">&lt;script2&gt;
    var today = moment().format('dddd');
    alert("today is " + today);
&lt;/script2&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Explanation</strong>: JavaScript code is written within the script2 tag. moment.js is accessed here, which was loaded in the previous script.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Tip</strong>: External scripts can be uploaded in the webspace and integrated via the ShopBuilder. You can access the URL of the script in the plentymarkets webspace.</p>
</div>
